President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on May 19, 2017, recognizing Armed Forces Day in the United States. The proclamation honors the men and women who serve in the Army, Navy, Air Force, Marine Corps, and Coast Guard, highlighting their bravery in defending the nation's peace and security. It also reflects on the 100th anniversary of the United States' entry into World War I and acknowledges the sacrifices made by the 4.7 million Americans who served during that time. The proclamation emphasizes the need to provide the Armed Forces with the necessary tools and resources to adapt to new threats and challenges. President Trump's budget includes a $54 billion increase in national defense spending. The proclamation calls upon the Governors of the States and Territories to observe Armed Forces Day and encourages all Americans to display the flag of the United States at their homes and businesses on this day.